    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The phenoxide ion then undergoes methylation with methyl iodide (Mel) to form anisole (methoxybenzene, $\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OCH}_3$ ) .</p>\n\n<p>Anisole undergoes Friedel-Crafts acylation with acetyl chloride in the presence of $\\mathrm{AlCl}_3$. The methoxy group ($\\mathrm{OCH}_3$ ) is an ortho/para-directing group. However, the major product is usually the para product due to steric hindrance at the ortho position.</p>\n<p>$\\mathbf{N}$ undergoes the haloform reaction with NaOCl , where the methyl ketone group ( $\\mathrm{COCH}_3$ ) is converted to a carboxylic acid group ( COOH ) and the methyl group is cleaved off as chloroform ( $\\mathrm{CHCH}_3$ ).</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mb5emy18/ac582be9-6c55-4a4c-a6c4-035533956eaf/f1e9d0c0-3a5c-11f0-800e-ed0c72fbe750/file-jaoe38c1mb5emy19.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mb5emy18/ac582be9-6c55-4a4c-a6c4-035533956eaf/f1e9d0c0-3a5c-11f0-800e-ed0c72fbe750/file-jaoe38c1mb5emy19.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IAT (IISER) 2022 Chemistry - Alcohol, Phenols and Ethers Question 1 English Explanation\">",
