    "explanation": "<p>When Acetophenone ethylene ketal reacts with dilute hydrochloric acid $(\\mathrm{HCl})$ in water $\\left(\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}\\right)$, it undergoes acid hydrolysis. The reaction breaks the ketal back into the original carbonyl compound acetophenone and ethylene glycol.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ma3v30cr/e31a35f7-d7a4-48d5-9163-07f06ada4566/7a0a65b0-25b7-11f0-b83d-2702e74f88d9/file-jaoe38c1ma3v30cs.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ma3v30cr/e31a35f7-d7a4-48d5-9163-07f06ada4566/7a0a65b0-25b7-11f0-b83d-2702e74f88d9/file-jaoe38c1ma3v30cs.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IAT (IISER) 2020 Chemistry - Alcohol, Phenols and Ethers Question 2 English Explanation\">",
